
SunCheck

WHY: 

1) Raise awareness about harmful chemicals in sunscreen;
	-marine life adversely affected; algae, dolphins, coral
	-show visual of projected impact based on usage
 	-Minimize the purchase and use of sunscreen that contain the harmful chemicals
	-in hopes of decreasing the amount of chemicals released into the ocean

2) To efficiently let users know if their sunscreen contains 1 or more of the 10 primary harmful chemicals
	-word detection software to instantly detect chemical names
	
	
	
LINKS:
http://www.marinesafe.org/blog/2016/03/18/sunscreen-pollution/
https://www.seagoinggreen.org/blog/2018/2/12/how-is-sunscreen-actually-affecting-the-marine-environment
https://www.icriforum.org/sites/default/files/ICRI_Sunscreen_0.pdf






